<% content_for :title, "Push Notifications — Help" %>

<div class="flex gap-8 lg:gap-12">
  <aside class="hidden lg:block w-52 flex-shrink-0">
    <%= render "sidebar" %>
  </aside>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <%= render BreadcrumbComponent.new(items: [
      { label: "Help", path: help_path },
      { label: "Push Notifications", path: nil }
    ]) %>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Push Notifications</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-stone-500">Stay updated on your bookings without checking the app.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-stone-700">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Enabling Notifications</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            Once signed in, you'll see a <strong>Enable Notifications</strong> button in the top
            navigation. Click it and accept the browser permission prompt that appears. That's it —
            you're subscribed.
          </p>
          <p>
            Notifications work even when the app isn't open in your browser, as long as your browser
            is running in the background.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">What Triggers a Notification</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 text-sm">
          <ul class="space-y-3 rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-5">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 text-green-600">✓</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Booking confirmed</strong> — sent after your payment succeeds, with the date and time of your session.
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 border-t border-stone-100 pt-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 text-red-500">✕</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Payment failed</strong> — sent if your card is declined, so you know to try booking again.
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 border-t border-stone-100 pt-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 text-stone-400">✕</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Booking cancelled by the studio</strong> — sent if the studio cancels your session, along with a note about your refund.
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Disabling Notifications</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            To stop receiving notifications, click <strong>Disable Notifications</strong> in the top
            navigation (it replaces the Enable button once you're subscribed). You can also revoke
            permission directly in your browser settings.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Notifications Not Working?</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            Make sure your browser has permission to show notifications from this site. In most browsers
            you can check this by clicking the lock icon in the address bar. If you previously blocked
            notifications, you'll need to re-enable them there before the Enable button will work again.
          </p>
          <p>
            Notifications require a modern browser (Chrome, Edge, Firefox, or Safari 16.4+). They are
            not supported in private/incognito windows.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
